review_blob: I was never a big fan of ales. Too fruity for my taste. I personally prefer imperial stouts. Anyway...bottled. Scent of flowers. It had a strong astringent citrus (a mix of orange and lemon)taste to it. Bitter finish. I would probably rate it higher if I were a ale person...
Bottled. Smelled like Very thick chocolate and coffee taste, with a slight bitter cocoa finish. Very good imperial stout indeed!
Bottled. No skunky scent. Like many lagers, it had an ever so bland taste with hints of corn. Astringent finish. Not bad...

Bottled. Picked this up at an Italian grocery in Niles, Illinois. 3 bottles for 99 cents was too good to be true when the best before date was back in 2003! Anyway, strong skunky scent and flavor. Forst could be a decent pilsener if it is fresh, but as for the 2 bottles, I used it to wash my hair.
Bottled. Very bland with a strong astringent finish. I couldnt help it but think that I was drinking straight-up alcohol. Next...
Bottled. Hoppy scent. Had a malty taste with hints of grass and corn. Clean crisp finish. Not bad.
Loved it! Loved it! Loved it!  Strong chocolate scent. Bottled. Had a bouquet of coffee and chocolate taste with slight hints of caramel. Beautiful.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottled.  No skunky scent. Bland, but had faint corn taste, and a slight astringent aftertaste. Could be better.
Bottled. No skunky scent detected. Ever so bland with faint grassy and hoppy hints. Clean aftertaste. Then again, the best before date is on July 2007. A decent lager.
Sickly sweet beer! It had a syrupy honey aftertaste. Dont get me wrong, this is one damn good beer! Thanks Mike K!
beer_name: Avery The Beast Grand Cru Ale

review_blob: Bottled. Had a dark, roasted, slightly burnt chocolate/coffee taste. Aftertaste is as bitter as drinking coffee. Highly recommended!
Bottled. No odor detected. It was ever so bland like many other lagers, but it had a weird blood aftertaste. Not a good beer.
Bottled. Had a flowery aroma. Strong herbal, citrus state. Spicy, astringent finish. Recommended.
God awful! Skunky scent, watery taste, and an offensive, sour finish. To the bloody bins!

Bottled. Best before December 2006. Yet another bland, uninspiring lager; but very easy to drink without any awful aftertastes like that God-forsaken Polar from Venezuela. Bonus points for Pilsener because my folks used this to cook ribs last Saturday, and those ribs were pretty good!

Bottled. No scent detected whatsoever. Has no taste, HOWEVER, it had an odd chemical aftertaste to it. I dont know how to describe it but this is really bad beer. The chemical aftertaste scared me so, for my healths sake, I decided not to finish Polar. AVOID!

Bottled. Oh no! I smell urine, could it be...nah. Yet another bland, uninspiring lager with faint malty taste and highly carbonated. Had this ice-cold, and it is refreshing during the summer. One final note, my 6-packs best before date was back on December 19, 2005!

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Bottled. It had a very refreshing fruity taste. It had a strong but sweet citrus flavor to it. Clean finish. Wasnt like the other hefe-weizens that were old and tasted like soy sauce! A great beer to combat the warm summer!

This is my 100th beer. An OK lager, or maybe I was lucky enough to get a decent 6-pack that didnt rot enroute to the U.S. Hoppy scent, watery taste with faint malty taste and a dry, astringent finish. I love the bottle though. Among Southeast Asian lagers, Singha and Tiger will forever be behind my beloved San Miguel Beer...
Bottled. As soon as I sipped it, I wondered if this is even considered beer! Its like drinking a combination of coffee and chocolate! Had a dry finish though, it made me want to drink water...
Bottled. Had an excellent, citrus flavor with a sharp finish, like a radler. Strong carbonation makes this easy to drink. I was very impressed.

Bottled. Got this at La Unica Grocery on W. Devon Avenue in Chicago. By the way, La Unica is THE place for hard-to-find Latin American beers in Chicago to my knowledge. They carried Pacena, Pilsener Ecuador, Polar, and Club Colombia. Anyway to the beer, had a hoppy scent so I was kind of hopeful...alas, once again I was disappointed by the taste. Bland, uninspiring, had a chemical corn, astringent aftertaste to it. Since its scorching hot right now, I guess pale lagers are a refreshing thirst quencher before drinking better beers in the fall/winter.
Bottled. Shared this with my uncle from the Philippines. Pours a light golden body. Refreshing if bland with a lemon twist. Not bad, a good starter beer.
Bottled. Pours a lovely dark, golden brew with no particles. Lovely cocoa scent. Salvator had a very strong fruity taste with hints of burnt caramel. Not bad.

Bottled. Pours a nice light golden body with a little too much head in my opinion. Had a bitter, herbal taste to it. Slightly fruity but was overshadowed by the herbal taste. Nevertheless, it is still a very good ale.
Bottled. Pours a dark caramel body. Strong dark, slightly burnt chocolate/coffee flavor with hints of spicy hints. Nice caramel finish. Clearly one of the best beers Ive ever had! Goodbye lagers!
Bottled. Dark brown, coffee-like body. Strong chocolate, caramel flavor with hints of spicy herbs. It had a nostalgic flavor to it!  Very good!
Bottled. Pours a beautiful dark caramel body with a big head. Strong dark/burnt chocolate/coffee taste. Pretty good!
Bottled. Strong skunky scent, very bland. I may have to cut back on lagers!
Bottled. Picked this at Tenutas Italian Deli in Kenosha, Wisconsin. Slightly skunky and ever so bland. It goes down pretty well, so I guess its an OK beer.
Bottled. Floral aroma, large head. Strong fruity flavor and a bitter malty aftertaste. Highly recommended!
Very bland, tastes like water with some corn/rice flavor. Poor. It is refreshing on a 90-degree day!
Bottled. Pours a golden body with a good head. Has a crisp, light fruity flavor, possibly citrus. Clean, bitter, astringent finish. A pretty good beer!
Bottled. Pours a light golden body with a large head. Strong malty flavor. Had a fruity, citrus taste to it. Bitter finish. An OK beer.
Bottled. Pours a light golden body with small head. Strong grassy/hoppy scent. Malty flavor. OK finish. An OK beer.
Bottled. Slight skunky scent, which seems to be the norm for some European lagers. Malty flavor with a citrus twist to it. Astringent finish. Not a bad beer.

Bottled. Pours a large, yet rapid disappearing head. Strong malty taste. Singha reminded me of the time I tried Red Stripe: it had a rubbing alcohol taste to it. Bitter, astringent aftertaste. Surprisingly good and high alcohol content too! One final note, Singha or "singa" in Filipino means snot!

Ive always wanted to try this beer, since we couldnt get this in Illinois, so I drove across the border to Kenosha, Wisconsin to get a 6-pack. Bottled. Pours an amber body, and a frothy head. It had a strong skunky scent, so I prepared for the worst....tasted pretty good! Strong hoppy taste and an astringent finish. Pretty refreshing! I wasnt disappointed. Now that I had Kro 1664, I could finally now drink "real beer."
Has a sublime dark chocolate/coffee flavor. An excellent beer and a must try for all!
Bottled. Slight skunky scent. Malty flavor with faint grassy hints. An OK beer.
Bottled. Pours a light golden color. OK carbonation. Inoffensive scent. Crisp grainy taste. Surprisingly OK. I should drink more real beers!!!
Bottled. Pours a golden amber color. Well carbonated. Crisp grainy and malty taste. Grassy scent. Excellent finish. Lives up to its expectation! One of the best pilsners in the world!
Bottled. Pours a golden body. Grainy scent. It had a odd, fruity flavor for a pilsener. Decent finish. Good job Norway!
Bottled. Has a skunky, fruity scent to it. Hoppy taste, and an OK finish. My God, I should start drinking more real beers!
Bottled. Noticed small particles floating in the bottle. Pours a small head quickly and light amber color. Slight skunky scent. Grassy taste, ok finish. An OK beer. I love the label though!
Bottled, well-carbonated. Pours a small head quickly.  Hoppy scent. Slight grainy taste. Has a fruity zing to it. Inoffensive aftertaste.
Bottled. OK carbonation. Slight skunky scent. Pours a light amber color. Malty taste. Decent aftertaste. Typical lager.

Bloody awful. Too much carbonation, no taste whatsoever. Nice label though, but Budweiser Budvar kicks this poor imitations ass. Shame on you Anheuser-Busch for not allowing Budweiser Budvar to be sold under its original name!
Strong flowery scent. Lacked flavor but had a faint lemon taste. Easy finish makes it easy to drink. Not bad.
Bottled. Not bad, but was very grainy for my mouth. It also had a refreshing citrus flavor. Slight bitter finish.
